reviews.title: Delicious Meal and Peaceful Ambiance!!!

The desserts looked delish, but was to full to try any. They have a full bar for desired drinks. Seating is comfortable and ambiance is peaceful. May go back to taste other meals. Harlingen is a nice quaint town and walk is easy to get from place to place, or stroll around and see the architecture. Highly Recommended!

articleContent.title: Your go-to guide for dog-friendly travel

seoInfo.metaDescription: Traveling with your dog has never been easier—or more fun. Cities across the country boast pet-friendly hotels, parks, and activities. With CESAR® brand’s mission to make the world more pet-friendly and Tripadvisor’s top-rated spots, you can plan with confidence. Whether it’s a quick getaway or a bucket-list trip, our guides help you stay, play, and explore with your pup. Grab the leash and go!

In four days, you can take a big bite out of Barcelona. And not just its tapas—this city does small plates better than anywhere else on earth—but also its art, culture, and entertainment. From Gothic palaces to Gaudi masterpieces and from late-night concerts to fast-paced soccer showdowns, Barcelona seriously delivers.
Outdoor wonders and indoor hangouts worth exploring
How to make the most of three days in Melbourne from the best coffee spots and restaurants to iconic sights and art museums.

tripContent.title: The bourbon lover’s guide to Louisville
tripContent.description:
No trip to Louisville is complete without a proper sampling of world-famous Kentucky Bourbon. From centuries-old distillers to newcomers with their own modern twists, here's where you can get a taste of America's only native spirit on your next trip. 

Please drink responsibly.

tripContent.title: The Wanderer's guide to Saudi Arabia
tripContent.description: "When Laviai, Marsha, and I set out for Saudi Arabia with "The Wanderer" we had no idea how much this journey would change us. We expected stunning landscapes, rich history, and great food—but what we didn’t expect was how deeply we’d connect with the country and its people. From the moment we arrived, we were met with kindness and curiosity, and when we left, it felt as if we were saying goodbye to a home we'd only just discovered. This guide is our way of sharing our firsthand experiences. Whether you're planning your first visit or just curious about what makes Saudi Arabia so special, we hope our perspectives help you see this country with wide eyes, open hearts, and an endless sense of wonder." – Lina

reviews.title: Make a reservation. Warm welcome, everything top

reviews.title: Delicious, ask about the specials
reviews.text: Delicious food, nice service. Nice specials that you can choose from in addition to the menu. This also applies to a code d'buof. Beautiful piece of meat, they came to show me whether my husband was sure he was going to eat this. However, they should have also mentioned the price, 95,-!!! I was shocked when paying, but I didn't say anything because I was in shock for a moment. It was nice that way ;) but tip to mention this, not everyone could afford this!

reviews.title: No knowledge of allergies.
reviews.text:
Please indicate allergies when booking.
Main course was fine. Atmosphere is good.
Staff friendly.
Please mention allergies again when ordering dessert. She would pass it on to the kitchen.
Got the dessert, unfortunately with the ingredient I am allergic to. Reported this and received an apology. A new dessert was brought with once again the ingredient I am allergic to. Then just asked for the bill.
The next day I received an email with a link for feedback. Completed this.
Now a week and a half later and unfortunately no response.

reviews.title: Nice grand café in beautiful Harlingen
reviews.text:
It felt like a living room. Nice and attentive staff with a sense of humor. Generous portions. Warm and cozy. We felt at home.
Point of attention: at the round table near the coffee machines you are a bit bothered by the noise of the coffee machines (when grinding the beans?). This did not last long, but it did happen frequently. Idea: a partition between the coffee machines and the round table? But otherwise: nice grand café in beautiful Harlingen!

reviews.title: High tea
reviews.text: I had high tea with my friend. It was incredibly tasty and we had a wide choice of different types of tea such as fresh mint and ginger. First we got a platter of savory snacks and then another platter of sweets. Super friendly service and we were given a doggy bag because it was a bit much.. :) Definitely recommended!

reviews.title: Careless
reviews.text:
Went here last year with a discount voucher, it was not a success. The main course was called 'forest mushroom risotto' but only contained two shreds of mushroom. When we said something about it, the answer was 'yes, that's how we get it delivered' > so it is clearly not freshly made but only warmed up.
Went here again today, by accident because I didn't remember the name of the restaurant last time. For the daughter who has to eat gluten-free, there were no fries or potatoes with the burger 'for fear of cross-contamination via the fryer or oven'. That sounds conscious and therefore confidence-inspiring. But...... at dessert there were pieces of stroopwafel under her ice cream!!! She didn't expect that so she ate a piece. I said something about it at checkout and the answer was 'yes, I tried to remove it as much as possible'....
So bad, don't go here if you have gluten allergy. Or like freshly made food.

Snitsel natural came with sauce and a second attempt also went wrong. Strawberry coupe with ice cream without strawberries. And the drinking glasses were regularly empty. But we had a very nice evening.

reviews.title: Really a guest.
reviews.text: Delicious food, partly thanks to the extremely friendly and helpful manager in every way? We were really guests.

reviews.title: Delicious food in a beautiful establishment
reviews.text: Beautifully decorated restaurant with an excellent menu. Something for everyone. The staff is friendly and knowledgeable. The quality of the food is fantastic and the portions are serious. I would advise leaving room for the delicious desserts. It's that we have to drive three hours to get there, otherwise we would come back here regularly. Topper

reviews.title: Not a very successful outing
reviews.text: What was supposed to be a nice dinner for my birthday turned into a long sitting. We had a reservation early in the evening. When we arrived it turned out that the place was already full and they were able to show us a table. After 45 minutes we asked if we could order something... No, there were no cards available so we couldn't order food yet... Finally we looked for the online menu and when they came again (with a card) ) ordered immediately. After another long wait, the starter finally arrived. The main course then took almost an hour to arrive. We swallowed that and left. No dessert and no follow-up, we would have had it. Sat there for almost three hours. The food was good, that wasn't the problem. The lack of staff and too many customers was not a successful combination. In any case, I won't be back for dinner anytime soon.

reviews.title: Majestic at the Giant
reviews.text:
Very nice and cozy restaurant. You can eat at the front of the road, inside and in the back of the garden. The staff is friendly and the service runs smoothly. We really enjoyed it, it was very tasty and more than enough. Enjoyed a great and relaxing meal, highly recommended!

reviews.title: Very pleasant
reviews.text: We were passing through and stopped for lunch. The place is very pleasant with its interior decoration and its outdoor terrace at the back. The staff are welcoming and friendly. The contents of our dishes (lunch menu) were fresh, delicious and gourmet.

reviews.title: Nice meal
reviews.text: Nice trendy restaurant with garden. It is a large space, split into two parts, so it doesn't feel too big. Nice meal. Oysters, prawns à la plancha and tournedos were delicious. Crème brûlée with goat cheese, honey, sweet cranberries and rye bread was a bit too sweet/heavy in our opinion. Sole was good, with delicious roasted vegetables. In addition, a lot of attention from the service; really interested in what we thought of it.

reviews.title: recommended

Delicious food and extremely attentive and friendly service.
we can definitely recommend this restaurant.
